{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "It is the largest model in the general language model (GLM) series with 130 billion parameters.",
    "Tsinghua University proposed the GLM based on auto-regressive blank filling for three tasks: natural language understanding (NLU) [64], conditional generation tasks [65], and unconditional generation tasks [66].",
    "GLM performed well in all three tasks.",
    "In the same year, Google released the PaLM 2 model [67], with a massive parameter count of 5.4 trillion and a token count of 780 billion.",
    "When trained via Google's next-generation PathWay distributed training framework [68], the PaLM achieved state-of-the-art performance on hundreds of small-sample language understanding and generation benchmarks.In 2023, Meta AI introduced the LLaMA model [69] collection, which includes four sizes (7 B, 13 B, 30 B, and 65 B)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
